# Golden Squirrel Interviewer

## Overview  
This project enables users to create AI-assisted interview-style videos with creators and celebrities. Users provide a script, which the AI verifies against available clips, suggests edits if needed, and then generates a stitched video mashup for sharing.

---

## Features  
- Script input and verification with AI suggestions  
- Side-by-side script review and approval interface  
- Semantic clip search from indexed video datasets  
- Automated video stitching and branding overlays  
- Video preview and export functionality  

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites  
- Node.js 18+  
- Access to OpenAI API (GPT-4)  
- Supabase account (or equivalent for storage)  
- FFmpeg installed or available in your cloud environment  
- Vector database (Weaviate or Pinecone) account

### Setup

1. Clone this repository:  
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-org/golden-squirrel-interviewer.git
   cd golden-squirrel-interviewer
Install dependencies:

bash
Copy
npm install
Set environment variables (create .env):

ini
Copy
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_key
SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_key
VECTOR_DB_API_KEY=your_vector_db_key
Run development server:

bash
Copy
npm run dev
Usage
Navigate to http://localhost:3000

Enter your interview script and submit for verification

Review and approve AI-suggested script edits

Generate and preview the interview video mashup

Download or share the video on social platforms
